Human Rights Watch reported on forced resettlements in Tibet and neighboring Tibetan areas as part of China's development plan to bridge the economic gap between the west and east.
Tibetan herders were compelled to sell their livestock and move to new townships, disrupting their traditional way of life.
Farmers in Gansu province are being displaced to combat desertification, despite protests.
The government's focus on soil erosion control and water conservation has shown progress, reversing erosion in some areas.
However, challenges persist, with soil loss and desertification threatening agricultural livelihoods in various regions, necessitating relocation and conservation efforts.
